The paper deals with the compressibility of signals and random variables, which is a topic of interest in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of entropy measures also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The focus on innovation processes, which are often used in stochastic modeling, could also place the paper in the sub-category of stochastic processes (cs.SI).
